title: No Tsunami after major 7.0 South Pacific Earthquake
text:
No Tsunami after major 7.0 South Pacific Earthquake Adv: 
Jul 10, 2015 Adv: 
No Pacific-wide Tsunami is expected according to the US Geological Center in Hawaii after major 7.0 earthquake hit off the Solomon Islands in the South Pacific Ocean 
The quake hit at 12.41 UTC time 
155km (96mi) SSW of Dadali, Solomon Islands 165km (103mi) W of Honiara, Solomon Islands 470km (292mi) SE of Arawa, Papua New Guinea 877km (545mi) SE of Kokopo, Papua New Guinea 887km (551mi) E of Alotau, Papua New Guinea 
No reports of injuries or damages has been reported at this time
